Mach Terminal builds on the following third-party open-source software,
each under its own license:

- Tauri (https://tauri.app) — Apache-2.0 / MIT
- portable-pty / wezterm-* (https://github.com/wezterm/wezterm) — MIT
- xterm.js (https://xtermjs.org) — MIT
- React (https://react.dev) — MIT
- Vite (https://vite.dev) — MIT
- reqwest, serde, tokio, tracing, keyring, and other Rust crates — see
  their respective Cargo manifests and license files.

The full dependency license set is reproduced in distributed builds and
can be regenerated from the lockfiles (package-lock.json, Cargo.lock).
